        <p class="TableTextEmphasis">mc-footnote-format</p>
        <p class="TableText">Determines the footnote format for numbers in the text. For example, you can change the format to uppercase alpha (e.g., A, B, C) or lowercase Roman (e.g., i, ii, iii). You can also replace the number with a symbol, such as an asterisk.</p>
        <p class="TableText" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">
            <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Footnotes/Editing-Footnotes/Editing-Footnote-Number-Formats.htm">Editing Footnote Number Formats</MadCap:xref>
        </p>
